title: [Spoilers] Daenerys can't possibly die
body:
We left season seven with the white walkers breaching the wall. It seems a given than Jon has gotten her pregnant, which means 9 months would have to pass for her to give birth and I can’t see the show jumping nearly that far before the final battle. It seems if she does die, her baby will too.



Source: https://ift.tt/2QxGGbW

summary: [SPOILERS] The villians in this show are let off way too easy
title: [SPOILERS] The villians in this show are let off way too easy
body:
Apart from Ramsay who was eaten by dogs, the others get pretty quick “tame” deaths compared to other characters.

Like Joffrey just being poisoned, he didnt even know wtf was happening and died fast. Roose and Tywin both get killed by their sons and in both cases its a surprise. Compare that with Ned who was publicly humiliated as a traitor and had to shit on his honor to save his daughters, Robb who saw his wife and unborn baby being murdered and Catelyn who basically went crazy at the end etc. and its nothing



Source: https://ift.tt/2C2exG9

body: Day 9 features Lyanna Mormont (played by Bella Ramsey ) from @gameofthrones 🖤 A badass young lady, thrust into a position of power and responsibility at an extremely young age, in possession of the honor, integrity, confidence, and loyalty that most people lack, and a pioneering feminist in Westeros. Don’t need to say much more other than when I grow up I wanna be Lyanna Mormont 😂👍💪🙌👑
